\b Decorator\

\b0 Wrapping a class in a \'91decorator\'92 class which adds functionality while keeping the original functionality in tact i.e. the decorator has a method with the same signature as the wrapped class that calls the wrapped class\'92s method and does extra stuff.\
\

\b Facade\

\b0 Using a \'91facade\'92 class to abstract away the complexity of other classes, providing a simpler interface to the user.\
\

\b Observer\

\b0 A way of ensuring that changes in state are cascaded to other objects e.g. the \'91subject\'92 has methods for adding observers and calls \'91update\'92 on all observers when the state changes.\
